1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Billie-Eilish-at-the-Grammys.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="Billie Eilish at The 67th Annual Grammy Awards, airing live from Crypto.com Arena in Los Angeles, California, Sunday, Feb. 2. (Photo by Francis Specker/CBS via Getty Images)" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Billie-Eilish-at-the-Grammys.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Billie-Eilish-at-the-Grammys-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Billie-Eilish-at-the-Grammys-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Billie-Eilish-at-the-Grammys-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Billie-Eilish-at-the-Grammys-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Billie-Eilish-at-the-Grammys-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> West Yorkshire manufacturer Abraham Moon &amp; Sons&#39; mill has shared their “complete surprise” after learning that <a href="/artists/Billie-Eilish">Billie Eilish</a> wore a baseball cap made from their cloth at the 2025 <a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/grammys">Grammys</a> .</p><p> While attending the 67th Grammys ceremony – which was held in Los Angeles this past weekend (February 2) – the singer sported a yellow sports jersey and an LA Dodgers hat with two small union flags and the word “Moon” embroidered on the side panel.</p><p> The logo belongs to Abraham Moon &amp; Sons, one of the last surviving woollen mills in the UK.该公司成立于1837年，并创建了出售给全球领先时尚和室内设计师的布。 Not all of the items that use Moon&#39;s cloth feature their logo but by luck, Eilish&#39;s Dodgers hat did. </p><figure id="attachment_3834761" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3834761" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3834761" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-conten